pipestream-proto-tools-protobuf-validation-protovalidate
========================================================

This module implements support for the protovalidate validation standard,
which was created by Buf Technologies, Inc. Its behavior is a derivative of
that standard: this project aims to be a compatible superset, so every
conformant protovalidate annotation validates identically here.

Vendored schema
---------------
This module vendors the protovalidate schema definition:

  src/main/proto/buf/validate/validate.proto

Vendored verbatim from the bufbuild/protovalidate project:

  Source:  https://github.com/bufbuild/protovalidate
  Version: v1.2.2
  Commit:  4baed765070e580226a0a30bf2a357cc027dc1f7
  License: Apache License 2.0 (see LICENSE-protovalidate)
  Copyright 2023-2025 Buf Technologies, Inc.

The vendored file is never modified, and its wire types remain under the
build.buf.validate package for exact compatibility. The semantics of the
buf.validate option namespace, and the protovalidate standard those options
express, are defined by the upstream project.

Original code
-------------
All other code in this module is original to pipestream-proto-tools, written
from the protovalidate specification and its conformance suite (not derived
from the upstream implementation source), and licensed under the repository's
MIT license.
